1. Set environmental variables

Make sure the following variables are set correctly:
LLVM_ROOT
SLICER_ROOT
APPS_ROOT

e.g.
LLVM_ROOT=/home/jingyue/Research/llvm
SLICER_ROOT=/home/jingyue/Research/slicer
APPS_ROOT=/home/jingyue/Research/apps

2. Install libraries

sudo apt-get install libbdd-dev libbz2 openjdk-6-jdk libboost-regex-dev

3. Building LLVM 2.7

git clone git@repair.cs.columbia.edu llvm

TODO

4. Building common modules

cd llvm # The directory you just cloned in last step
cd bc2bdd
make
make install
cd ..
cd common
./configure --with-llvmsrc=<path to LLVM source code> --with-llvmobj=<path to LLVM object files> --prefix=<path to LLVM installation directory>
make
make install
cd ..

5. Building Slicer

git clone git@repair.cs.columbia.edu slicer
cd slicer
./configure --with-llvmsrc=<path to LLVM source code> --with-llvmobj=<path to LLVM object files> --prefix=<path to LLVM installation directory>
make
make install

6. Test Slicer

cd tests
make build
make run

If no crashes or assertion failures, all test cases are passed. 
